							<h5 class="mb-1 text-center">English</h5>
							<p>
								Artificial Intelligence (AI) techniques open up promising
								ambitions in several areas.<br />
								The field of public health and patient care is one of the most
								critical areas for the development of a country.<br />
								Diseases represent a risk that threatens citizens in their
								physical, mental and financial states.<br />
								In a country like Algeria where public health is provided by the
								state, this care will cost the national treasury dearly.<br />
								With AI techniques that consider: collection of patient data,
								processing by filtering and classification, reasoning and
								decision-making, recommendation and action control, AI is in a
								positive position to contribute to the development and
								improvement of the field of health.<br />
								This application of AI, on the other hand, requires the
								establishment of physical infrastructure (networks of
								data-collecting sensors, communication networks, servers for
								storing large volumes of data) as well as the development and
								optimization of software solutions that deal with
								classification, filtering, learning, diagnosis and decision
								making.<br />
								The coupling of IA, IoT and Cloud Computing represents an
								important lock for the success of this integration of AI in
								health-care domain.<br />
								The objective of this event organized by the mixed team TIASM
								(Technique de l’IA pour le soutien de la médicine) is to gather
								a set of researchers (professors and PhD students) with a set of
								professionals and doctors to discuss and present some of the
								recent researches that concern the use of AI in health-care
								domain.
							</p>
